This is a list of the symbols of the States and union territories of India. Each State and Union territory has a unique set of official symbols.

States[edit]

Andhra Pradesh[edit]

Title Symbol Image Notes
State animal Blackbuck (Antilope cervicapra)
State bird Rose ring parakeet (Psittacula krameri)[1]
State flower Jasmine (Nymphaeaceae)[2]
State tree Neem (Azadirachta indica)[3]
State fish Murrel(Channa striata)[2]
State seal Ashoka lot Link to image
State song Maa Telugu Talliki (To our Mother Telugu)

Title Symbol Image Notes
State animal Mithun (Bos frontalis)[4][5][6]

State flower Foxtail orchid (Rhynchostylis retusa)[4][5][6]
State tree Hollong ( Dipterocarpus macrocarpus)[7][8]
State seal Ashoka lot Link to image

Karnataka[edit]

State flag Karnataka flag Adopted unilaterally by state government in 2018
State seal Coat of arms of Karnataka
Song 'Jaya Bharata Jananiya Tanujate'[42] (Victory to you Mother India)

state butterfly : Southern Birdwing

Kerala[edit]

Main article: List of Kerala state symbols
Title Symbol Image Notes
State animal Indian elephant (Elephas maximus indicus)[43][44]
State bird Great hornbill (Buceros bicornis)[43][44]
State fish Green chromide (Etroplus suratensis)[45] Green chromide was designated state fish by Government of Kerala in 2010.
State flower Kanikonna (Cassia fistula)[43][44]
State tree Coconut tree (Cocos nucifera)[43][44]
State Fruit Jackfruit Jackfruit was Declared as Official State Fruit of Kerala on 21 March 2018.[46]
State seal Seal of Kerala The emblem portrays two elephants guarding the state and national insignias.
The state insignia is the conch-shell of Lord Sri Padmanabha and the national insignia is the famous Lion Capital.[47]
